-- SEC Proposes Requiring Hedge Funds, LBO Firms to Register With U.S. Agency
-- B y   J e s s e   H a m i l t o n
-- 2010-11-19T16:19:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/sec-proposes-requiring-hedge-funds-lbo-firms-to-register-with-u-s-agency.html
U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission proposed requiring hedge funds and private-equity
funds to register with the agency, aiming to expand oversight as
required by the Dodd-Frank financial-regulation law.  SEC commissioners voted to seek comment on the proposal at
a meeting in Washington today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jesse Hamilton in Washington at 
 jhamilton33@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lawrence Roberts at 
